			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">griever wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">$DF19:B5 75&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;LDA $75,X @ $0144 = #$00&nbsp; &nbsp;A:00 X:CF Y:FF P:NvUbdIzC<br />$DF1B:8D 07 20&nbsp; STA $2007 = #$00&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;A:10 X:CF Y:FF P:nvUbdIzC<br /></div><br />What the hell? STA $2007 = #$00           A:10 &lt;--!!! where did this 'A=$10' come from :shock:</div>
<br />
<br />Zero Page,X mode wraps to zero page if the addition of X causes it to exceed $00FF.  The debugger here is showing an incorrect read address (and thus, an incorrect read value).  That LDA is <em>actually</em> reading from $0044... which apparently contains $10.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

